HEADWORD: Uncloister
<hw>Un*clois"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>cloister</ets>.]</ety> <def>To release from a
cloister, or from confinement or seclusion; to set free; to
liberate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

